        <p class="ActionDetail">&#160;</p>
        <table style="border-left-style: Solid;border-top-style: Solid;border-right-style: Solid;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-left-width: 2px;border-right-width: 2px;border-top-width: 2px;border-bottom-width: 2px;border-left-color: #5f5f5f;border-right-color: #5f5f5f;border-top-color: #5f5f5f;border-bottom-color: #5f5f5f;width: 100%;border-spacing: 0px;border-spacing: 0px;" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
            <col style="width: 15.979%;" />
            <col style="width: 84.021%;" />
            <tr valign="top">
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 15.979%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #c9c9c9;border-left-width: 3px;border-left-style: Solid;border-left-color: #ffffff;border-right-width: 3px;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-top-width: 3px;border-top-style: Solid;border-top-color: #ffffff;" bgcolor="#C9C9C9" width="15.979%">
                    <p style="font-weight: bold;">Purpose</p>
                </td>
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 84.021%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #eaeaea;border-right-width: 3px;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-top-width: 3px;border-top-color: #ffffff;border-top-style: Solid;" bgcolor="#EAEAEA" width="84.021%">
                    <p>Register and notify unauthorized critical parameter changes. Critical parameters are typically used to optimize the system (i.e.: reduce energy consumption). These parameters are rarely changed and it may be important for the site manager to be notified (via text message - SMS - fax or e-mail) of any unauthorized changes.</p>
                    <p>Changes may be made by personnel using field device keyboards or directly via PlantVisor PRO. Each single change is recorded in a log. Notifications may per single change (for each parameter changed) or all changes (one for all parameters changed within a set control interval). 
 </p>
                    <p>The user in charge monitors changes and for each unauthorized change may:</p>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>restore default values (values compared to values read from the field at control), </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="2">
                            <p>leave values changed (to become default values for next control).</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top">
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 15.979%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #c9c9c9;border-left-color: #ffffff;border-left-style: Solid;border-left-width: 3px;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-width: 3px;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;" bgcolor="#C9C9C9" width="15.979%">
                    <p style="font-weight: bold;">Description</p>
                </td>
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 84.021%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #eaeaea;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-width: 3px;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;" bgcolor="#EAEAEA" width="84.021%">
                    <p>A summary map always displays the values routinely read from the field. The following registrations appear in the log:</p>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>changes to single parameters due to unauthorized changes;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="2">
                            <p>changes to single parameters due to restored default values;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="3">
                            <p>default value readings.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top">
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 15.979%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #c9c9c9;border-left-color: #ffffff;border-left-style: Solid;border-left-width: 3px;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-width: 3px;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;" bgcolor="#C9C9C9" width="15.979%">
                    <p style="font-weight: bold;">Procedure</p>
                </td>
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 84.021%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #eaeaea;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-width: 3px;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;" bgcolor="#EAEAEA" width="84.021%">
                    <p>Parameter control must first be set up, enabled and activated. </p>
                    <p>To setup parameter controls:</p>
                    <ol start="1" style="list-style: decimal;margin-top: 0cm;list-style-type: decimal;">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>Set the list of critical parameters (see <a href="Controllo_paramentri__Configurare_la_funzione.htm">Function setup</a>) indicating the control interval, notification addressees and list of user profiles with editing permission.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="2">
                            <p>Set default values (see <a href="Controllo_parametri__leggere_i_valori_di_riferimento.htm">Reading default values</a>).</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="3">
                            <p>Start <b>Parameter control </b> (see <a href="Controllo_Parametri__Avviare_fermare_il_monitoraggio_dei_parametri_critici.htm">Starting/stopping critical parameter monitoring</a>).</p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <p>Once the control has started, the following operations are possible:</p>
                    <ol start="1" style="list-style: decimal;margin-top: 0cm;list-style-type: decimal;">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>Monitor real-time values read from the field (see <a href="Controllo_parametri__Monitorare_le_modifiche_non_autorizzate.htm#Monitorare_i_valori_letti_dal_campo">Monitoring values read from the field</a>)</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="2">
                            <p>Analyze any unauthorized changes recorded in the log (see <a href="Controllo_parametri__Monitorare_le_modifiche_non_autorizzate.htm">Monitoring unauthorized changes</a>) </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="3">
                            <p>Restore default values for single changes  (see <a href="Controllo_parametri__Monitorare_le_modifiche_non_autorizzate.htm#Ripristinare_i_valori_di_riferiment">Restoring default values</a>)</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="4">
                            <p>Stopping parameter control (see <a href="Controllo_Parametri__Avviare_fermare_il_monitoraggio_dei_parametri_critici.htm">Starting/stopping critical parameter monitoring</a>).</p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
